properties.areaDesc: Wind River Mountains West; Upper Green River Basin Foothills
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 2:40PM MST until January 14 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...New round of Snow for the West Tonight through Tuesday
Afternoon...

.Snow will increase in coverage and intensity tonight and
continue through Tuesday afternoon.

* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5 inches from
Pinedale to Bondurant to the Hoback Canyon. Mountain snowfall
of 6 to 9 inches is expected.

* WHERE...West Wind River Mountains and Upper Green River Basin
Foothills.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 5 PM MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Tuesday morning.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Those planning outdoor activities should
be prepared for the snow and cold.
properties.instruction:
The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 PM MST TUESDAY
